<h1>Android</h1>

<article><a name="cameraview"><h2>CameraView</h2></a>
<p class="Stats"><time datetime="2017-08">August 2017</time> • $(loc ../CameraView cameraview/src/main) • Java • Unlicense</p>
<p>A view that shows what the camera sees.</p>
<p>Supports orientation changes, fits the preview image into the available view space and works with Gingerbread (minSDK 9) or better.</p>
<ul class="ProjectLinks Separator">
<li><a href="https://github.com/markusfisch/CameraView">Source</a></li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/markusfisch/CameraView/releases">Releases</a></li>
</ul></article>

<article><a name="scalingimageview"><h2>ScalingImageView</h2></a>
<p class="Stats"><time datetime="2015-11">November 2015</time> • $(loc ../ScalingImageView scalingimageview/src/main) • Java • Unlicense</p>
<p>An ImageView that transforms its drawable according to touch input.</p>
<p>Supports rotated images and keeps transformation when you exchange the image for another one with a different size.</p>
<ul class="ProjectLinks Separator">
<li><a href="https://github.com/markusfisch/ScalingImageView">Source</a></li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/markusfisch/ScalingImageView/releases">Releases</a></li>
</ul></article>

<article><a name="swipeimageview"><h2>SwipeImageView</h2></a>
<p class="Stats"><time datetime="2017-01">January 2017</time> • $(loc ../SwipeImageView swipeimageview/src/main) • Java • Unlicense</p>
<p>An ImageView that can be used to swipe between images and supports pinch/zoom gestures to explore the current image.</p><p>Think of Google Photos.</p>
<ul class="ProjectLinks Separator">
<li><a href="https://github.com/markusfisch/SwipeImageView">Source</a></li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/markusfisch/SwipeImageView/releases">Releases</a></li>
</ul></article>
